Your friend determines whether he can draw a triangle with angle measures of $50^\circ$, $60^\circ$, and $70^\circ$. Is your friend correct? Explain.

\begin{center}
$50^\circ + 60^\circ + 70^\circ = 180^\circ$

Because the sum of the three angle measures is equal to $180^\circ$, these angles will form a triangle.
\end{center}
